  1. create a 25 \(\times\) 25 matrix with autoregressive structure with \(p = 9/10\), every element in the matrix should be equal to \((9/10)^{|i-j|}\) where i is the row index and j is the column index. Report the row and column sums of this matrix.
n = rep(0,25)
p = 9/10
newmatrix = matrix(n, nrow = 25, ncol = 25, byrow = TRUE)
for (i in 1:25) {
  for (j in 1:25) {
    newmatrix[i,j] = p ^ abs(i-j)
  }
}
x = colSums(newmatrix)
y = rowSums(newmatrix)

  1. now resample the elements of x with replacement 10000 times, and compute and store the statistic (mean(x’) - mean(x))/se(x’) at each iteration where x’ corresponds to the resample of the elements of x. Call the vector which contains these reasampled statistics `resamples’. Use an apply function for this part.
resamples = rep(0, 1e4)
new1 = function(i) {
  y = sample(x, replace = TRUE)
  i = (mean(y) - mean(x)) / (sd(y) / sqrt(length(y)))
  result1 = c()
  result1 = append(result1, i)
  return (result1)
}

new2 = function(i2, l) {
  result2 = sapply(1:l, new1)
  return (result2)
}

resamples = new2(x, 1e4)
  1. run the command `hist(resamples, breaks = 20)’ to make a histogram, include this histogram in your assignment.
hist(resamples, breaks = 20)

  1. Write 3 separate loops: a for loop, while loop, and repeat loop that give the same result. The result should be the cumulative sum of Days in jail among Black people whose Arrest Ages 18-24 with Student as Employment status within the CCSO Bookings Data.
#for loop
newgetOne = filter(ccso, RACE == "Black" & EMPLOYMENT.STATUS =="Employed - Full Time" & Age.at.Arrest <= 26 & ccso$Age.at.Arrest >= 15)
temp = dim(newgetOne)[1]
for (i in 1:temp) {
  a = a + as.numeric(newgetOne[i,]$Days.in.Jail)
}
a
## [1] 186275.8
#while loop
n = 1
result = 0
while(n <= temp){
  result = result + as.numeric(newgetOne[n,]$Days.in.Jail)
  n = n + 1
}
result
